title: Woman's Cap, late 17th–18th century
medium:
Medium: linen
Technique: bobbin lace, needle lace
description: Bonnet-like cap of un-dyed linen gathered to arched opening at nape and at crown. Arch at crown filled with reticella; narrow reticello band running along front edge on either side. Broad band of bobbin lace forms rectangular brim with confronted animals and double-headed eagle on a heavy mesh ground.
